<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Shriver Home Damaged by Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	POTOMAC, Md. (AP) -- Investigators are trying to determine the  
cause of a fire Wednesday that damaged the home of Eunice Kennedy 
Shriver and her husband, Sargent Shriver. 
</P>
<P>
	The blaze damaged portions of the second floor and attic of the  
Potomac River mansion where the Shrivers have lived since the 
mid-1980s. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fire began in a concealed area between the second and  
third floors,'' said Capt. Barry Reid of the Montgomery County Fire 
and Rescue Department. 
</P>
<P>
	Eunice Shriver -- a sister of Sen. Edward M. Kennedy, D-Mass.,  
the late Robert F. Kennedy and assassinated President John F. 
Kennedy -- was at home when the blaze broke out. She escaped the 
house unharmed. 
</P>
<P>
	Reid said about 85 firefighters and 25 pieces of equipment were  
involved in extinguishing the blaze. One firefighter was treated at 
the scene for heat exhaustion. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
