<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-10 04:00:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boys Charged With Attempted Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- A 13-year-old boy and his 12-year-old brother are  
accused of trying to kill a 3-year-old girl by beating and kicking 
her and forcing her into a clothes dryer. 
</P>
<P>
	``I told her in a mean voice to get in the dryer,'' the older  
boy told the Detroit Free Press in a story published today. ``She 
was turning around inside and after a few moments, I let her out.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Wayne County Family Court Referee Richard McKnight on Wednesday  
ordered the boys held in lieu of $20,000 bonds pending a June 17 
hearing. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl was hospitalized in serious condition with burns to her  
chest and back, bruises to her face and neck, and a possibly 
lacerated liver. 
</P>
<P>
	She and her mother had been staying with the boys' family  
because their utilities had been shut off. 
</P>
<P>
	The woman left her daughter and infant son with the boys'  
16-year-old sister when she went to work Monday. The 13-year-old 
told police his sister went out that night, leaving the children 
with her brothers. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy told the newspaper he punched and kicked the girl  
because she wouldn't stop crying, then told her to get in the 
dryer. 
</P>
<P>
	The mother noticed injuries on her daughter when she returned  
home about 2:30 a.m. Tuesday, according to police. 
</P>
<P>
	Assistant Wayne County Prosecutor John Knappmann said the girl  
may also have been sexually abused and purposely burned with a 
candle. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can't comprehend it,'' the boys' father said Wednesday. ``If  
he's guilty of hurting that kid, I'm all for the system 
straightening him out.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
