<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mother Kills Husband, Two Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- A mother of four who had been  
treated for depression fatally stabbed her husband and wounded 
their 8-year-old daughter on Thursday, then killed herself and two 
younger children by setting the house on fire. 
</P>
<P>
	The daughter, who also suffered burns, called police and escaped  
to a neighbor's home. The fourth child, a 6-month-old boy, suffered 
burns. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was obviously in a state of trauma and shock. It was  
marvelous she had the presence of mind to call,'' Police Chief 
James Shay said. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said Kelly Silk, 32, asphyxiated in the fire. She  
had apparently used a chemical to start the blaze and may have been 
caught up in the first flash of fire. 
</P>
<P>
	Charles Silk, 39, died of stab wounds. The two children,  
Jennifer, 3; and Jonah, 2, died of smoke inhalation and burns. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said Mrs. Silk overdosed on the antidepressant Prozac  
last May. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a real shocker,'' said neighbor Austin Harlow, who got  
regular visits from the family who came to see his horses. ``She 
took care of the kids.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Family friend Joe Amato said Mrs. Silk became depressed after  
the birth of her third child, about 18 months ago. 
</P>
<P>
	``It took her ... a good three, four months to overcome it,''  
Amato told WFSB-TV. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
