<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  United 3, Fusion 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Richie Williams had a goal and an assist as  
D.C. United beat the Miami Fusion 3-1 Thursday night in Major 
League Soccer, extending its winning streak to six. 
</P>
<P>
	By handing the Fusion its seventh loss in eight games, the  
first-place United pulled eight points ahead of Columbus in the 
Eastern Conference. 
</P>
<P>
	Roy Lassiter, who scored his league-leading 12th goal, and Ben  
Olsen had first-half goals for D.C (9-3). 
</P>
<P>
	Henry Gutierrez scored for the Fusion (4-10), which fell to 0-7  
on the road. 
</P>
<P>
	Lassiter gave D.C. the lead in the eighth minute, extending his  
point-scoring streak to seven games. 
</P>
<P>
	Geoff Aunger, in the middle of the penalty area, flicked a  
header that Lassiter tapped past goalkeeper Jeff Cassar from five 
yards out. 
</P>
<P>
	United outshot Miami 10-4 in the first half, and eight of those  
shots came during a 14-minute stretch that produced Olsen's goal 
and a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 32nd minute, Olsen made a run down the center of the  
penalty area, where he accepted Williams' neatly threaded pass. 
Olsen's right-footed shot glanced off Miami's John Maessner and 
slipped inside the right post. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams made it 3-0 in the 58th minute on a fallaway shot from  
the top of the goalie box, depositing the ball into the upper left 
corner past Garth Lagerway, who replaced Cassar at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
	Gutierrez scored on a diving header in the 69th minute.  
</P>
<P>
	D.C. played without midfielder Marco Etcheverry, serving a  
one-game suspension. 
</P>
<P>
	Welton, playing in his second game with the Fusion since he was  
acquired June 1, had an assist in his 100th MLS game, the first 
international player to reach that milestone in the league's 
four-year history. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
