<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Chris Doleman Finally Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Defensive end Chris Doleman officially  
retired Thursday from the San Francisco 49ers. 
</P>
<P>
	Doleman had first announced his retirement after the 49ers'  
20-18 playoff loss to the Atlanta Falcons this past season. 
</P>
<P>
	Doleman finished the regular season with 15 sacks, the  
second-highest total in his 14-year career. He had 21 in 1989 while 
with Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	He finished with 142 1/2 sacks to rank fourth all-time in NFL  
history. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to the Vikings and the 49ers, Doleman also played  
for the Falcons. 
  	   	
</P>
