<HEADLINE> Texas Death Row Inmate Loses Appeals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- Two courts rejected appeals Thursday by a  
man who could be the first Canadian executed in the United States 
since 1952. 
</P>
<P>
	The Texas Supreme Court and a three-judge panel of the 5th U.S.  
Circuit Court of Appeals both let stand a lower court ruling that 
found Texas' clemency process constitutional. 
</P>
<P>
	They ruled in response to petitions from Joseph Stanley Faulder,  
