the beating and stabbing of a 75-year-old woman during a robbery at 
her home in 1975. 
</P>
<P>
	Delegations from Canada, which has no death penalty, have made a  
series of trips to Austin in unsuccessful attempts to have the 
execution called off. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright has 
also asked for a reprieve for Faulder. 
  	   	
