<HEADLINE> 10th Death in Arkansas Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) -- An Air Force mechanic died Thursday  
from injuries he suffered in last week's crash of an American 
Airlines jet, raising the death toll to 10. 
</P>
<P>
	Master Sgt. Jeffery Stewart, 33, died of multiple injuries. He  
was on life support after Flight 1420 crashed off the end of a 
runway in a thunderstorm, broke apart and caught fire. 
</P>
<P>
	Nine people died at the scene, including the pilot. More than 80  
of the 145 passengers and crew members were injured. 
</P>
<P>
	Stewart, who had been based on Okinawa Island in Japan, was  
coming to Little Rock Air Force Base for training in jet-engine 
repair, Master Sgt. Scott Martin said. 
  	   	
</P>
