<HEADLINE> Horse Trainer Is Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP)-- Trainer Louis Albertrani has been suspended 15  
days and fined $2,500 after Carney's Creek, a horse in his care, 
tested positive for a prohibited substance after finishing third in 
Aqueduct's second race on April 11. 
</P>
<P>
	The horse tested positive for a prohibited substance,  
Clenbuterol, a broncho-dilator banned by the New York State Racing 
and Wagering Board. 
</P>
<P>
	Carney's Creek has been declared disqualified and unplaced in  
the revised order of finish of the race in question and his owners, 
Paraneck Stable, denied any share in the purse. 
  	   	
