<HEADLINE> Corixa To Buy Ribi ImmunoChem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HAMILTON, Mont. (AP) -- Corixa Corp. plans to buy medical  
research company Ribi ImmunoChem Research Inc. for $56.3 million in 
cash and stock. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials with Corixa said they plan to continue operating in  
Hamilton, where Ribi has a facility to produce pharmaceuticals. 
</P>
<P>
	Ribi employs about 115 people in Hamilton, said Kris Dyszynski,  
the company's director of licensing, though she did not say if any 
jobs would be lost. 
</P>
<P>
	Robert Ivy will resign as Ribi chairman and chief executive, and  
will serve as a consultant to Corixa. 
</P>
<P>
	Ribi and the Seattle-based Corixa research treatment and  
prevention of disease through vaccines and other products. 
</P>
<P>
	Corixa chairman Steven Gillis said Ribi will complement Corixa's  
work in cancer, infectious disease and autoimmune disease. 
</P>
<P>
	Ribi developed a cancer vaccine, Melacine, that is under  
regulatory review in Canada. Last winter, the company announced it 
had developed a key ingredient in a more powerful hepatitis B 
vaccine. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
