<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dismore Eecovers From Crash in Texas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Mark Dismore recovered from a Thursday  
afternoon crash to outrun teammate Scott Sharp for the pole 
position for the Longhorn 500 IRL race at Texas Motor Speedway. 
</P>
<P>
	Dismore, 42, a national go-kart champion at age 11, lapped at  
215.272 mph. 
</P>
<P>
	Sharp, who also drives for the Kelley Racing team and who paced  
both of Thursday's practice sessions, qualified second at 214.839 
mph. Tyce Carlson was third at 214.417 and Greg Ray fourth at 
213.805. 
</P>
<P>
	Defending champion Billy Boat was 11th of 26 entrants at 211.671  
mph. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not been an up day actually. It was a bit of a downer.  
But this sure makes up for it,'' Dismore said. 
</P>
<P>
	In his first afternoon run, Dismore made contact with an outside  
retaining wall exiting turn 4. His car became loose between turns 3 
and 4, and there was light damage to his right front wheel. 
</P>
<P>
	Dismore, who broke his neck, both feet, right wrist and right  
knee in a crash during practice for the Indy 500 in 1991, climbed 
out of the car without assistance. After evaluation in the infield 
care center, he was cleared to drive. 
</P>
<P>
	The laps were well off the track one-lap qualifying record of  
225.979 mph set last September and the one-lap race record of 
228.012 set by Tony Stewart a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	It marked the Indy Racing League's first competitive event on a  
high-banked oval since the ill-fated VisionAire 500 at Concord, 
N.C., on May 1 in which three spectators were killed by flying 
debris. 
</P>
<P>
	The IRL moved to reduce speeds slightly beginning with the  
Longhorn 500 by lowering maximum RPMs from 10,300 to 10,000. It 
follows a reduction in the RPMs from 10,500 in 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Dismore began racing karts in 1968 and won 40 grand national  
kart races through 1989. He made his Indy-car debut at Mid-Ohio in 
1989, won the Formula Atlantic Pacific Division championship in 
1990. 
</P>
<P>
	He came to Indy but did not qualify in 1992-93. He won the 24  
Hours of Daytona in 1993 and at Nazareth in 1994 in his only 
Formula Atlantic start. His best IRL finish is fifth twice. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a great place for a race,'' Sharp said. ``It's fast,  
it's smooth, there are multiple grooves, and that means great 
racing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Saturday's race is the fifth in the IRL's 11-race season.  
</P>
<P>
	Race speeds Saturday are expected to drop more than 3 mph  
because with the reduction in RPMs. In theory, lower speeds make 
the cars more driveable, resulting in fewer crashes. 
</P>
<P>
	TMS is a 1.5-mile quad-oval with 24-degree banked turns, similar  
to Concord and Atlanta Motor Speedway, which was built for heavier 
and slower stock cars. IRL races have been staged at TMS and 
Concord since 1997 and at Atlanta since 1998. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
