<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ralston Purina To Spin Off Eveready </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Ralston Purina Co. plans to spin off its  
Eveready Battery Co. Inc. subsidiary to shareholders. 
</P>
<P>
	Ralston Purina, based in St. Louis, is composed of Ralston  
Purina Pet Products, a dog and cat food manufacturer, and Eveready, 
which produces dry cell batteries and flashlights. 
</P>
<P>
	The spinoff, which gives shareholders of Ralston Purina new  
tax-free shares of Eveready Battery Company, will take about seven 
to 10 months to complete, the company said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The move will depend on a favorable tax ruling by the Internal  
Revenue Service and a final approval by the Ralston Purina board of 
directors. 
</P>
<P>
	In a related move, Ralston Purina co-CEO J. Patrick Mulcahy, has  
resigned from his position to focus more on the battery company. 
</P>
<P>
	W. Patrick McGinnis, who served as co-CEO with Mulcahy, has been  
named CEO of the company. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
