<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 46; Nasdaq Falls 20 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened lower. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is down 46 points in today's early going. Losers 
on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 9-4 lead over gainers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is down 20 points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is down six points. 
</P>
<P>
	Good news for Tokyo could be seen as bad news for Washington.  
</P>
<P>
	The Japanese economy expanded in the first quarter, the first  
sign of growth in a year and a half. 
</P>
<P>
	But that growth may be an indication that some of the shackles  
on the U.S. economy -- having to do with overseas weakness -- are 
about to be removed. 
</P>
<P>
	And some suggest that could lead to greater economic expansion,  
and possibly inflation in the U.S. 
</P>
<P>
	As a result, bond prices have been moving lower, sending the  
benchmark yield up to 6.5 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	It closed above six percent yesterday, for the first time in  
more than a year. 
</P>
<P>
	And analysts say that helped send blue-chip stocks to their  
second decline in a row. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
